Youth counselling  - basic knowledge of the theory and practice of counselling and youth counselling, youth counsellor skills
Information service - European Youth Information Charter, ERYCAObjectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose: To develop youth counselling skills and improve the skills necessary for implementing the principles of the European Youth Information Charter.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  - has basic knowledge of the theory and practice of counselling and youth counselling; - is aware of the contents of youth counselling and information service processes, their specifics and practical techniques; - knows different counselling techniques; - knows the European Youth Information Charter, and the principles of the service standard and ERYCA; - can survey the information needs of young people; - has practical experience in the counselling process; - can give an overview of the activities of a youth counsellor and information specialist.
